x4freetext: Self-supporting foils of Ti-46 and Ti-48, thickness
The target thicknesses was measured both by weighing
and by measuring the loss of 5.5-MeV alpha particles
The enrichment 81.02% of the Ti-46 target was
appropriately accounted for in the thickness, but no
corrections were made to the scattered yields.

x4freetext: The overall errors in the cross sections due to
uncertainties in target thickness, integrated charge
and solid angle are estimated, including counting
statistics, to range from ~5% to 11%.  At some larger
angles these errors come up to ~16%, primarily due to
low counting statistics.  The errors in the data are
shown wherever they exceed the size of the point on
